{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0154izTaLpHiir5GTQqMrpYf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it. The bilingual detection logic is IDENTICAL between iteration 18 and iteration 19 for this section. So the bilingual detection didn't change. The issue must be in something else.\n\nLet me look at what ELSE changed and could affect the scoring. The key changes in iteration 19 are:\n1. Section-label joins now allowed (changed blocking logic)\n2. joinsToProtect (new)\n3. pos0Compounds (new)\n4. Various hard filter changes\n\nHmm. Actually wait - the section-label blocking change could have a significant impact. In iteration 18: joins starting with section labels were always blocked. \n\nIn iteration 19: joins starting with section labels are allowed UNLESS `isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel`. SKLADNIKI is at line 9 and appears in ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS in iteration 19, so those joins are still blocked. But in the body text, some previously-blocked joins might now be generating new candidates that compete with \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" for the threshold.\n\nActually, could the key issue be simpler? Let me think about the `pos0Compounds` protection.\n\nAfter bilingual detection and Fix 2, the `selected` array is built from `scoredForThreshold`. There's a filter that identifies compounds at position 0, then removes any other candidates that are substrings of those position-0 compounds and appear later in the text. \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" is at position 0, so it's in pos0Compounds and...\n\nActually, let me trace through this more carefully. The individual words like \"zielona\" or \"fasolka\" would only be in `selected` if they survived the hard filters as standalone lines, which seems unlikely given how the filtering works. I need to look at what's actually in `selected` after the bilingual detection step.\n\nThe main candidate here is \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" at position 0, plus whatever body text made it through. Then the deduplication logic kicks in—it's checking if one title is a substring of another and keeping the shorter one...\n\nWriting deduplication logic... I'm checking whether those exact words appear as isolated lines in the file—\"zielona\" and \"fasolka\" don't show up on their own, though similar variations like \"zielonej\" and \"fasolk\" do appear. The real question is whether these shorter fragments would even qualify as candidates based on the garbling check and other filters. Looking at the diff between iterations 18 and 19, the bilingual detection logic stayed the same, but there are several new additions: metadata pattern matching, an always-block list for join labels, updated logic for joining multi-line sections that allows more flexibility when there are enough words and the label isn't blocked, plus new helper functions to identify cooking instructions and strip out parenthetical glosses and page numbers.\n\nFor this specific file, the most significant changes would be the revised join logic for 2-3 line sections and potentially the parenthetical stripping on single candidates. Let me trace through: \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has no parentheses, so the stripping function wouldn't affect it. As for the join logic change, it only applies to joins starting from section labels, not from regular lines, so that wouldn't have generated new candidates here either.\n\nActually, looking back at the diff more carefully — the logic shifted from blocking all joins when the first line is a section label to instead allowing the join but then checking if it should be blocked based on word count or specific label types. This is a meaningful difference in how section headers interact with the joining process.\n\nLet me check what section labels actually appear in this file and whether they'd be affected by this change. \"SKLADNIKI\" is marked as always-block, so it would still be prevented from joining. But I need to look at the commit message for 55b161b to understand what the actual intent was here.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4089,"cache_read_input_tokens":77370,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4089},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe1e814e-1a51-4be7-ba64-e09ed2a4511e","uuid":"cc55d631-62ae-45bd-b74f-87a5ef863491"}
